‹g¬]<?php exit; ?>a:1:{s:7:"content";O:8:"stdClass":9:{s:7:"term_id";s:4:"1191";s:4:"name";s:15:"Prostate Cancer";s:4:"slug";s:15:"prostate-cancer";s:10:"term_group";s:1:"0";s:16:"term_taxonomy_id";s:4:"1191";s:8:"taxonomy";s:7:"ailment";s:11:"description";s:4078:"<span style="font-weight: 400;">Prostate cancer is the cancer of the prostate, a small gland in men that produces the seminal fluid that transport and nourishes the sperm. Globally, 1 in 9 men experiences prostate cancer at a time in their life.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Prostate cancer is most common in older men as well as in African-American men. According to a diagnosis report, about 6 in 10 cases of prostate cancer are in men aged 65 or older, and it is uncommon in men less than 40 years. In fact, the average global age of diagnosis is about 66.</span>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Prostate Cancer grows slowly and is restricted to the prostate gland, where it is not life-threatening. However, even though some prostate cancer slowly grows without complications, others can be aggressive and spread to other areas of the body.¬† Detecting prostate cancer- when it‚Äôs only limited to the prostate gland- can be successfully treated.</span>

<b>Symptoms of Prostate Cancer</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">It may cause no symptoms in the early stages. However, at its advanced stage, below are some symptoms to examine:</span>
<ul>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Trouble with urinating</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Reduced amount of urine</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Blood in semen</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Bone pain</span></li>
 	<li><span style="font-weight: 400;">Erectile dysfunction</span></li>
</ul>
<b>Causes Of Prostate Cancer</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Doctors are unclear on what causes prostate cancer. Based on available information, prostate cancer occurs when the prostate cells start showing some abnormality. Mutations in the DNA of the abnormal cells make them grow and rapidly divide abnormally. The abnormal cells continue to function while others die off. These cells then grow to form a tumor which produces the seminal fluid.</span>

<b>Risk Factors Of Prostate Cancer</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">Certain factors trigger your risk of prostate cancer, they include:</span>

<b>Age</b><span style="font-weight: 400;">: chances of prostate cancer increases with age</span>

<b>Family history: </b><span style="font-weight: 400;">If men in your family have had prostate cancer in the past, chances are you may not be left out.¬†</span>

<b>How To Prevent Prostate Cancer</b>

<span style="font-weight: 400;">The following steps will help you prevent prostate cancer:</span>
<ul>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Include fruits and vegetables in your diet</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Choose a healthy diet over supplements</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Include exercise in your daily routine</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">Always maintain a healthy weight</span></li>
 	<li style="font-weight: 400;"><span style="font-weight: 400;">De-stress with meditation and other relaxing activities</span></li>
</ul>
